ge": {"prompt_tokens": 918, "total_tokens": 918}, "id": "b92b65f6-bac7-9e6e-b95c-feacdc3cb459"}, "input": {"input": ["躯体形式自主神经紊乱:\"躯体形式自主神经紊乱\" (Somatoform Autonomic Dysfunction) is a diagnostic condition classified as a subtype of somatoform disorder. It is characterized by symptoms of autonomic nervous system arousal or excitement that manifest across multiple organ systems. Notably, these symptoms occur in the absence of any identifiable structural or functional disorders in the affected organs. This condition reflects a psychosomatic presentation, where psychological factors contribute to physical symptoms, particularly those related to autonomic nervous system dysfunction.", "躯体形式障碍:躯体形式障碍（Somatic Symptom Disorder）是一种心理疾病，其特征是患者表现出多种躯体不适症状，但这些症状无法完全通过医学检查或器质性病变来解释。患者常常持久地担心或相信这些躯体症状，并反复陈述不适，不断要求进行医学检查。尽管检查结果通常为阴性，且医生解释其症状并无躯体疾病基础，患者仍对此表示怀疑。躯体形式障碍的病因多与心理因素相关，病程呈慢性波动性，预后通常不佳。治疗方面，主要以心理治疗为主，辅以药物治疗，旨在缓解患者的症状并改善其心理状态。", "躯体感染所致精神障碍:\"躯体感染所致精神障碍\"是一种由身体感染引发的精神障碍。这种精神障碍是由病毒、细菌、螺旋体、真菌、原虫等病原体引起的脑外全身性感染所导致的。具体而言，当这些病原体感染身体并引发全身性感染时，可能会对大脑功能产生影响，进而导致精神障碍的出现。因此，\"躯体感染所致精神障碍\"强调了感染与精神健康之间的直接关联，表明全身性感染是此类精神障碍的根本原因。", "躯体疾病:躯体疾病是指身体上的疾病，包括感染、代谢紊乱等，这些疾病不仅可能引发明显的身体症状，如疼痛、瘙痒、鼻塞和呼吸困难，还可能导致精神障碍，其严重程度与精神症状的轻重密切相关。躯体疾病的诊断需要仔细排除严重的器质性疾病，因为其症状可能与躯体形式障碍相似，但本质上是由于身体上的病理变化引起的。此外，躯体疾病如疼痛、瘙痒、鼻塞和呼吸困难等，还可能引起入睡困难和睡眠不深，进一步影响患者的整体健康和生活质量。", "躯体疾病及精神活性物质所致精神障碍:Mental disorders caused by physical illnesses or psychoactive substances, which can lead to acute or chronic mental health issues", "躯体疾病所致精神障碍:\"躯体疾病所致精神障碍\" (Mental Disorders Due to Physical Diseases) refers to a category of mental health conditions that arise as a direct consequence of physical illnesses. These disorders can manifest in both acute and chronic forms, often emerging during the most severe phases of the underlying physical disease. The condition is characterized by a range of psychiatric symptoms that are secondary to the primary physical illness. Management of these mental disorders typically occurs within general hospital settings, where both the physical and mental health aspects of the patient can be addressed concurrently. This condition underscores the intricate connection between physical health and mental well-being, highlighting the importance of a holistic approach to treatment.", "转换性感觉障碍:转换性感觉障碍主要表现为转换性感觉麻木和感觉丧失。症状表现不符合感觉神经的分布。其中，视觉障碍很少是完全性的，多为视野模糊或“管状视野”。\"", "转换性症状:转换性症状是一种由精神障碍引起的身体症状，通常与抑郁症或精神分裂症相关", "转换性癔症:A psychological disorder affecting voluntary motor or sensory functions, with symptoms suggesting neurological or general physical conditions. It is accompanied by psychological factors, and symptoms are not consciously produced or feigned. Diagnosis involves ruling out physical conditions and ensuring symptoms cause significant distress or functional impairment.", "转换性精神障碍:A psychological condition characterized by the conversion of mental stress into physical symptoms"], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-v3"}}}